parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including stalling, loss of power, and electrical fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The car stalls or loses power
electrical components malfunction
the car attempts to start on its own
lights come on and off
the alarm goes off
the car's systems behave erratically
and the car catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Keyless Access/TPMS Control Unit can cause the car's systems to malfunction, leading to safety risks, including stalling, loss of power, and electrical fires.
symptoms: The car's dashboard lights blink on and off
the headlights turn on
the car alarm intermittently alarms
the motorized steering wheel moves
and the car's systems behave erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning brake light can increase the risk of accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions.
symptoms: The brake light does not function properly
leading to warnings or citations from law enforcement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning rear view camera can increase the risk of accidents, as the driver may not have a clear view of the road behind them.
symptoms: The rear view camera remains on when shifting from reverse to drive
providing a view of the road behind the vehicle while driving forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the car to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The car stalls or loses power
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the car has difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission hesitation and slipping can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can be particularly dangerous when merging into traffic or crossing intersections.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or slips when accelerating

especially at low speeds; the transmission fails to deliver power to the vehicle for a second or two; the vehicle lurches forward under acceleration; the throttle becomes unresponsive; the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Miss-Shifting and Failure to Upshift
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission miss-shifting and failure to upshift can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can be particularly dangerous when merging into traffic or driving on the highway.
symptoms: The transmission miss-shifts
especially in the 25-40 mph range; the vehicle hesitates when taking off; the transmission fails to upshift when entering the freeway; the vehicle stays in one gear and will not upshift.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and loss of power can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can be particularly dangerous when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power while driving; the vehicle suddenly stops or hesitates; the engine makes ticking noises; the vehicle experiences a brief loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and acceleration issues can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates to accelerate
causing the driver to lose control or experience sudden deceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctions of the infotainment system can cause distractions, vision impairment, and safety risks while driving.
symptoms: The infotainment system freezes
navigation screen doesn't alternate between day and night modes
backup camera stays on while driving
and the system turns off and on repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The starter motor fails
the vehicle won't start
and the battery is fine but the vehicle won't shift to neutral.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Mirror and window issues can cause visibility problems and safety risks while driving.
symptoms: Side view mirrors and driver-side window glass freeze and won't open or roll down
and the rearview mirror breaks loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Software update issues can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: The "Auto Engine Idle Stop System Problem" message flashes
and the vehicle's engine may stall or hesitate to accelerate.
